; Paper & Ink — pnpm config
; Hoist ONLY @tailwindcss/postcss (exact package, no wildcard prefix).
; @tailwindcss/postcss itself is hoisted because:
;   1) frontend/postcss.config.json declares it as the only PostCSS plugin
;   2) Angular @angular/build:application's loadPostcssConfiguration() only
;      resolves postcss.config.json OR .postcssrc.json — NOT .js/cjs/mjs.
;   3) Without hoisting, .pnpm-resolved @tailwindcss/postcss still works
;      via Node resolve, but top-level resolution is a simpler code path
;      that mirrors what Angular does when it dispatches into PostCSS.
; `tailwindcss@4` itself stays nested under .pnpm/ — its bare
; PostCSS plugin entry would conflict with v4's split rule (plugin
; moved to `@tailwindcss/postcss`), so Angular's tailwindConfiguration
; path is bypassed entirely via the explicit postcss.config.json.
public-hoist-pattern[]=@tailwindcss/postcss
public-hoist-pattern[]=*@angular/build*
